docs.abstract: The findings of an internal affairs inquiry were made public for the first time at a disciplinary hearing against the officer, Daniel Pantaleo.
docs.snippet: The findings of an internal affairs inquiry were made public for the first time at a disciplinary hearing against the officer, Daniel Pantaleo.
docs.lead_paragraph: Internal affairs investigators who reviewed Eric Garner’s death determined that the officer who wrestled him to the ground in 2014 used a forbidden chokehold on him, a police supervisor testified on Monday during the officer’s disciplinary trial at Police Headquarters.

headline.main: Police Investigators Determined Officer Choked Eric Garner
headline.print_headline: Police Believe Officer Used Chokehold on Garner, Supervisor Says at Hearing

docs.abstract: The only public hearing into what happened to Mr. Garner — who exclaimed “I can’t breathe” as he died from a police chokehold — takes a microscopic view of a galvanizing event, our columnist writes.

docs.lead_paragraph: Over the last two weeks, a Staten Island man named James received an unexpected FedEx delivery. Then a certified letter. His phone rang constantly with calls from people on the 13th floor of Police Headquarters in Lower Manhattan. A taxi was parked outside his home, waiting for him.

docs.abstract: On HBO, Instagram — even Fox News — aspirants are having a meta debate: How do you counterprogram a reality-TV president?
docs.snippet: On HBO, Instagram — even Fox News — aspirants are having a meta debate: How do you counterprogram a reality-TV president?
docs.lead_paragraph: You can’t miss the peak of Beto O’Rourke’s 2018 Texas Senate campaign in HBO’s “Running with Beto.” Maybe you’ve already seen it, on your phone or in a Facebook post: Mr. O’Rourke responding passionately to a question about N.F.L. players taking a knee to protest racism and police brutality.

headline.main: In the Democratic Primary, the Media Hits Are the Message

docs.abstract: The doctor who performed an autopsy said Officer Daniel Pantaleo choked Mr. Garner with enough force to cause internal bleeding in his neck.

docs.lead_paragraph: The doctor who performed an autopsy on Eric Garner testified on Wednesday that a police officer choked him with enough force that it triggered a “lethal cascade” of events, ending in a fatal asthma attack.

headline.main: Medical Examiner Testifies Eric Garner Died of Asthma Caused by Officer’s Chokehold
headline.print_headline: Chokehold Caused Garner’s Fatal Asthma Attack, Doctor Says

docs.abstract: As students demand the renaming of buildings whose names pay tribute to polarizing historical figures, universities are at a loss for easy solutions.
docs.snippet: As students demand the renaming of buildings whose names pay tribute to polarizing historical figures, universities are at a loss for easy solutions.
docs.lead_paragraph: College campuses have long been centers of social foment and student activism. In the 1960s, they were magnets for protests over the Vietnam War, and more recently, the Black Lives Matter movement forced schools to confront issues of racial justice and inclusion.

headline.main: When the Names on Campus Buildings Evoke a Racist Past
headline.print_headline: On Campus, Finding Ways To Honor a Place’s History While Denouncing Racism
